ROHAN - Eomer and the Elite Rider are to be mounted at all costs. This gives them their strenght bonuses. Plus if you get them with a Spear/Sword and Bow, they are pretty hard to beat. The Lorien Swordsmen are your back up fighters along with Arwen. Leggy is for point and shoot. <br />
ELVES - Archery keeps those powerful Uruks from using their powerful(But conditional) gametexts, screw over Easterling deck, and trash Moria and Dunalnd.  The Lorien Swordsmen are your back up fighters along with Arwen and Haldir. Leggy is for point and shoot. <br />
ARCHERY and MOUNTS - OK - for the last time, this only helps Lorienswordsmen and Eomer - please don&#39;t give me anymore crap about this.  There are reasons for BOW AND MOUNTS.<br />
<br />
Minions <br />
Ferny takes away, for the most part, Gondorian Rangers game texts and roaming over all.<br />
---Added Fear  because people like to use Allies<br />
---Added Drawn to it&#39;s Power (which should be self explanatory - but for those of you who don&#39;t know what that card does - your minion wins add a burden)...You are out to slow down and somewhat burdenize your Opponent.  This is not the best Shadow side ever, but it&#39;s pretty gosh darnit good.<br />
<br />
SITES: <br />
Play them as they come....Hopefully you will be able to play to your sites....<br />
<br />
BIDDING: It just depends on who or what you are playing against and whether you want to play to your opponents site or yours...  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
